This is a Next.js 16 App Router project using TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, 

Drizzle ORM with Postgres (Supabase), and NextAuth.js v5 for authentication.

Architecture rules:

- Use server components by default. Only use "use client" when the component 

  needs interactivity (onClick, hooks, state).

- All API routes go in app/api/ using Route Handlers.

- Use Recharts for all charts and data visualization.

- Use lucide-react for icons.

- Mobile-first responsive design.

- The app uses a bottom tab bar for navigation, NOT a hamburger menu or sidebar.

Tab structure (bottom nav):

- Budget (stub)

- Planner (stub)  

- Home (stub)

- Portfolio (active, primary view)

- Settings (stub)

Design direction:

- The single source of truth for ALL visual design is EMBER-DESIGN-SYSTEM.md. Read it before touching any UI.

- Warm-paper aesthetic: flat surfaces separated by hairline rules and whitespace, NOT boxed white cards with shadows. At most one soft-shadow hero card per view.

- Consume design tokens only (CSS custom properties in app/globals.css / the Tailwind utilities that point at them). Never hard-code a hex color, font family, or radius in a component.

- Type: Newsreader for headlines/reflection, Hanken Grotesk (tabular-nums) for data/UI.

- NO stoplight red/green. Growth is sage (--ds-sage); the single accent is terracotta (--ds-terra). Text is soft espresso, never pure black.

- Voice: gentle mentor, growth/garden metaphors, never scold (see §7).

File organization:

- /components/layout/ — TabBar, Header

- /components/portfolio/ — chart, account list, groupings

- /components/ui/ — shared primitives (buttons, cards, inputs)

- /lib/ — utilities, db client, plaid client

- /drizzle/ — schema
